SIMPLE: prevailing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prevailing
<hw>Pre*vail"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having superior
force or influence; efficacious; persuasive.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Saints shall assist thee with <qex>prevailing</qex> prayers.</q>
<rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Predominant; prevalent; most general; <as>as, the
<ex>prevailing</ex> disease of a climate; a <ex>prevailing</ex>
opinion.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> See <er>Prevalent</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prevailingly</ent>⟦br⟧
